erlin described a ‘downcast, stigmatized Jewish population’, terrorized and powerless in face of displacement, expulsions and the increasing incarceration of the Jewish population in ghettos, and it predicted that ‘the process of destruction is not yet complete’. The volume documents the drive by the occupiers systematically to confiscate the property of the Polish Jews, and the different, often chaotic and conflicting strategies for displacing Jews in the annexed territories and in the General Government. The volume shows a range of reactions by the non-Jewish population of Poland to the escalating persecution of the Polish Jews. It also shows the efforts by Jewish organizations to publicize their plight abroad, to withstand the onslaught on their communities and to manage daily life in the increasingly desperate conditions of the ghettos. Learn more about the PMJ on https://pmj-documents.org/  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zEurope. 0aJewsxPersecutionszEuropevSources. 0aJewsxPersecutionszGermanyvSources. 4aHolocaust. 4aJudenverfolgung. 4aJüdische Geschichte. 4aPolen. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh  aHolocaust.  aPoland.  ajewish history.  apersecution of the jews.1 aFriedrich, Klaus-Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPearce, Caroline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831106879030 cprintz978311068737840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311068779840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110687798423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110687798/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  